parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the auto park brake system can cause the parking brake to engage unexpectedly, leading to loss of control and increased risk of accidents, especially on steep grades or when driving at high speeds.
symptoms: The parking brake applies unexpectedly while driving
the brake pedal goes to the floor
the brakes feel spongy or ineffective
the vehicle feels like it's in neutral while driving downhill
the brake fluid level drops rapidly
the brakes fade or become completely ineffective on steep grades.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A brake fluid leak can cause the brakes to fail, leading to loss of control and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: Brake fluid leaks from the actuator under the coach
the brake fluid level drops rapidly
the brakes feel spongy or ineffective.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: An electrical system short circuit can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power while in motion, increasing the risk of accidents or injuries, and may also lead to faulty or malfunctioning electrical components.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or loses power while in motion
the dashboard lights flicker or turn on and off
the tail lights malfunction or turn on and off
the vehicle experiences sudden electrical failures.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the dual wheel axle can cause the motorhome to become unstable and off-balance, leading to loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: The dual wheel axle breaks away from the chassis
the motorhome shifts from the frame
the vehicle becomes off-balance
unusual noises or vibrations from the axle area.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Transmission Slipping or Jumping Out of Gear
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission slipping or jumping out of gear can cause the vehicle to roll or move unexpectedly, even when the engine is off and the transmission is in park, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle jumps out of gear
the vehicle rolls or moves unexpectedly
the transmission slips or hesitates
unusual noises or vibrations from the transmission area.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine overheating can cause the vehicle to stall, leading to a loss of power and control, which can increase the risk of accidents, especially in hot weather.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or shuts down while driving
the temperature gauge is in the red zone
the coolant light is illuminated
the engine overheats
steam or smoke is visible from the hood.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A failed heat shield can cause a fire hazard, especially when the catalytic converter is hot, which can lead to a vehicle fire, potentially causing injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The heat shield under the coach is unwelded or loose
the catalytic converter is overheating
there is a burning smell or smoke coming from the underside of the vehicle.
